news.title: Mysuru: Over 1,000 Muda sites allotted disregarding laws and regulations
news.para: Muda officials failed to specify under which rules sites were allocated in the files, as revealed by the Lokayukta in its report to the special court, Bengaluru.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board allottees cry harassment over rule tweak, lax service delivery
news.para: The issues related to CHB's "poor" delivery of services and procedural complexities were taken up in a recent meeting of the administrator's advisory council and the CHB board of directors.

news.title: YEIDA to allow 8,000 property owners to pay for farmers’ aid in four instalments
news.para: Apart from allowing the payments to be made in instalments, the board also approved a medical college on 20 acres in Sector 17, adopted a partially uniform industrial plot allotment policy, and addressed delayed constructions across multiple sectors off the Yamuna Expressway.

news.title: From April, pay property tax in Bidhannagar on app
news.para: "The civic body wants to introduce BBPS to bring more convenience to taxpayers, allowing them to pay their property tax through a mobile app. The process to tie up with a bank has been initiated for the system to be introduced," said a BMC official.

news.title: Apartment complexes can now get skywalk link to Hyderabad metro stations
news.para: A decision to this effect was taken during a comprehensive mobility planning meeting between HMRL managing director NVS Reddy and HMDA metropolitan commissioner Sarfaraz Ahmed and confirmed in an official release on Monday.

news.title: Resolve all land acquisition issues in Agra amicably: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: To expand the urban limits and set up greenfield business and residential layouts land had to be aggregated in Rahankalan and Raipur localities along the inner ring road in the city of Taj.

news.title: Flats allotted by PMRDA structurally stable but need repairs for leakages: CoEPTU report
news.para: A Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority official said that the concerned developer has been told to complete all the repair works for leakages within a month.

news.title: Sale deeds for apartments to resume in April: Odisha minister
news.para: He said talks are on with the development authorities and all bottlenecks will be removed by the month-end. "There are some issues with part plot and apartment registrations for some time," Pujari said.

news.title: Sebi permits all HFCs to invest in security receipts by asset reconstruction companies
news.para: ARCs are set-up to acquire bad loans from banks and financial institutions after appropriate haircuts and issue security receipts (SRs).

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM orders immediate FIR against Ansal Group
news.para: During a review meeting of the Housing and Urban Planning Department, the chief minister emphasised that Ansal Group's "fraudulent practices" against homebuyers will not be tolerated. He instructed officials to take strong action against all responsible officers of the company.

news.title: ED identifies assets worth thousand of crores in searches against WTC Group & Bhutani Group
news.para: ​The raids were conducted on February 27 at a dozen locations in Delhi, Noida (Uttar Pradesh) and Faridabad and Gurugram (both in Haryana) against WTC Group and its promoter Ashish Bhalla, and Bhutani Group and its promoter Ashish Bhutani under the provisions of Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), the federal agency said in a statement.

news.title: Tata Katcon leases 77,800 sq ft industrial space from Malpani Group in Pune’s Chakan
news.para: The exhaust & emission solutions provider is set to commence its operations at the new facility at Malpani Industrial & Logistic Park this month.

news.title: Oberoi Group to open two new resorts in Rishikesh
news.para: The Oberoi Group executive chairman Arjun Oberoi said: “These two resorts reflect our unwavering commitment to expanding our presence in remarkable destinations.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body grants 80% concession to 12,000 property owners
news.para: The scheme offered an 80% concession on fines valid until Feb 28. 12,000 property owners collectively received a total concession of Rs11.83 crore, paying a total of Rs19 crore.

news.title: Cement demand to cross 640 MTPA by FY30: UltraTech
news.para: The cement demand was at 424 MTPA in the financial year which ended on March 31, 2024, according to the investor presentation, a copy of which was submitted to exchanges last week.

news.title: Mumbai: Pranav Constructions files for an IPO to raise Rs 392 crore
news.para: The IPO, with a face value of Rs 10 each, combines fresh issuance of Rs 392 crore with an offer for sale of up to 28,56,869 equity shares by the promoter and investor selling shareholders.

news.title: Australia's property market stabilizes in February amid rate cut : CoreLogic data
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic showed prices across the nation rose 0.3% in February from January, ending three months of declines or no growth

news.title: Zuari Infraworld & Gangothri Developers to develop housing project in Hyderabad at Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: Spanning across 9.4 acres, this upscale development is being executed by Gangothri Group, with Zuari Infraworld serving as a development manager.

news.title: China's second-hand home prices fell by 0.4% in February: Report
news.para: Prices of second hand homes fell 7.3% year-on-year on average in February, the report said, while the average price of new builds in the same 100 cities increased by 2.7%.

news.title: Cement sector to grow 6-7% in 2025-26: Report
news.para: Most companies (21 out of 25) saw a yearon-year decline in EBITDA margins, but higher operating leverage and lower input costs improved margins quarter-overquarter.
